abstract: >
  DepressionRisk-ML is a machine learning project developed to predict the risk of depression among university students.
  It integrates multiple classification algorithms, including KNN, SVM, and MLP, with a complete preprocessing pipeline,
  cross-validation methodology, interactive Streamlit application, and reproducible training structure. This work aims
  to support research and experimentation in mental health prediction using open and transparent machine learning tools.
